- I'd say so.

474
00:52:08,292 --> 00:52:11,420
- May I videotape your house?
- Of course.

475
00:52:13,548 --> 00:52:15,383
- I'm sorry.
- That's all right.

476
00:52:15,967 --> 00:52:18,010
I'll just turn this on...

477
00:52:24,350 --> 00:52:28,437
- Is this for television?
- No.

478
00:52:28,813 --> 00:52:32,525
I'm from a travel agency.
We specialize in Japan.

479
00:52:32,525 --> 00:52:35,778
Japanese tourists want to see
how typical Czechs live.

480
00:52:36,863 --> 00:52:41,617
- Would they come to our house?
- Yes, with an interpreter.

481
00:52:46,038 --> 00:52:51,502
If you're interested
we can go upstairs. Follow me.

482
00:52:57,216 --> 00:53:00,094
- Do you talk?
- Who? The two of us?

483
00:53:00,428 --> 00:53:02,555
Do you talk during meals?

484
00:53:03,306 --> 00:53:08,102
- Yes, a little.
- We talk a lot.

485
00:53:09,228 --> 00:53:16,068
We've had some quiet applicants.
That's not what we want.

486
00:53:16,444 --> 00:53:19,864
Actually we talk
all the time. Right, Dad?

487
00:53:21,073 --> 00:53:24,619
- Do you have a dog?
- No. -No problem.

488
00:53:25,494 --> 00:53:30,166
We'll provide one. Get small dog
that doesn't shed much.

489
00:53:31,042 --> 00:53:35,755
Hanka's staying in this bedroom
now. And here's the bathroom.

490
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:42,720
Excellent. You could walk
the dog, watch some TV.

491
00:53:43,596 --> 00:53:45,640
We could do that.

492
00:53:46,599 --> 00:53:51,520
- But the focus will be on food.
- What do you mean?

493
00:53:51,812 --> 00:53:54,815
- I'd say we're going to eat.
- Exactly.

494
00:53:55,149 --> 00:54:00,446
The Japanese want to know how
typical Czechs act during meals.

495
00:54:07,703 --> 00:54:08,996
Come in.

496
00:54:11,874 --> 00:54:16,712
- Am I disturbing you?
- Not at all. Come in.

497
00:54:20,007 --> 00:54:22,927
At the hospital
you offered to pay me back.

498
00:54:23,970 --> 00:54:28,015
- And the offer still stands.
- Now there is something I need.

499
00:54:29,058 --> 00:54:30,768
What is it?

500
00:54:36,315 --> 00:54:40,361
No, I'm sorry.
How would I do that?

501
00:54:47,410 --> 00:54:49,578
No, that wouldn't work.

502
00:54:59,463 --> 00:55:04,135
For my next trick I need
a volunteer from the audience.

503
00:55:06,387 --> 00:55:09,682
Sir, why don't you
come up here? Don't worry.

504
00:55:12,393 --> 00:55:13,936
Come right up.

505
00:55:19,150 --> 00:55:22,236
Get inside.
Don't worry. You'll be fine.

506
00:55:23,404 --> 00:55:25,990
You'll be fine... Perhaps.

507
00:55:28,617 --> 00:55:30,119
This is...

508
00:55:31,370 --> 00:55:33,372
I'll shut the door.

509
00:56:06,030 --> 00:56:10,868
- Am I to believe he disappeared?
- It sounds silly, doesn't it?

510
00:56:10,868 --> 00:56:15,748
- It sure does. -But it's true.
- This is a very bad joke.

511
00:56:16,165 --> 00:56:19,377
Ondrej has never pulled
silly stunts like this.

512
00:56:20,336 --> 00:56:23,798
I am not leaving until
you give me my husband back.

513
00:58:31,592 --> 00:58:32,676
Good afternoon.

514
00:58:33,469 --> 00:58:35,930
- May I help you?
- Are you Mrs. Cerna? -Yes.

515
00:58:37,348 --> 00:58:39,892
I've come to inspect
your gas appliances.

516
00:58:39,892 --> 00:58:42,645
- Come in. The gate's open.
- Thank you, ma'am.

517
00:58:50,778 --> 00:58:53,781
Stop making those awful faces!

518
00:58:56,242 --> 00:58:59,495
Are they even going
to watch me shave?

519
00:58:59,954 --> 00:59:02,206
We can still cancel out.

520
00:59:03,123 --> 00:59:09,004
When you think about it,
we could prevent wars.

521
00:59:10,256 --> 00:59:13,467
- In Kosovo, say?
- Doubtful.

522
00:59:14,802 --> 00:59:18,430
But if the Americans
had visited Vietnamese families,

523
00:59:18,430 --> 00:59:24,228
- there wouldn't have been a war.
- Wars break my heart.

524
00:59:25,104 --> 00:59:29,275
I can't bear to see
those children and poor people.

525
00:59:29,567 --> 00:59:31,944
And meanwhile we are so happy.

526
00:59:34,280 --> 00:59:37,908
- I'm not all that happy.
- Yes, you are.

527
00:59:39,451 --> 00:59:42,496
Happy is what
those people will never be.

528
01:00:11,358 --> 01:00:15,529
- Is everything all right? -Yes.
- I didn't even offer you a drink.

529
01:00:15,529 --> 01:00:19,199
- Do I owe you anything?
- No, these inspections are free.

530
01:00:19,199 --> 01:00:21,076
- Fine. Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

531
01:00:26,332 --> 01:00:28,876
- Did we have company?
- No.

532
01:00:29,668 --> 01:00:33,714
- How do you explain the flowers
in my room? -Which flowers?

533
01:00:34,673 --> 01:00:39,511
- I don't believe it.
- Actually, the gas man was here.

534
01:00:39,970 --> 01:00:43,223
- What did he want?
- He came to inspect the stove.

535
01:00:43,557 --> 01:00:46,769
But we don't have a gas stove.

536
01:00:50,356 --> 01:00:51,398
Hello?

537
01:00:52,650 --> 01:00:54,068
Ondrej?

538
01:00:56,153 --> 01:01:00,616
Not having a gas stove is
no reason to get hysterical.

539
01:01:09,375 --> 01:01:11,001
"Record Your Mother."

540
