Back to our contest. A friend
of mine likes surprising me.

541
01:01:20,052 --> 01:01:24,348
Sometimes it's quite unpleasant,
but now I'll surpise him.

542
01:01:24,682 --> 01:01:28,143
Recently he gave me
a tape of his mother.

543
01:01:30,229 --> 01:01:34,733
So, Robert. A big hello
to you and your mom!

544
01:01:40,531 --> 01:01:42,241
I've improved.

545
01:01:44,576 --> 01:01:49,081
For example, I go by garbage
cans without taking anything.

546
01:01:49,081 --> 01:01:51,792
- I had a mess tin here.
- Really?

547
01:01:54,461 --> 01:01:58,799
Last time someone threw away
a high power vacuum cleaner.

548
01:01:59,091 --> 01:02:01,427
- Are you recording this?
- Yup.

549
01:02:06,181 --> 01:02:09,184
- That's good.
- Do you have anything to drink?

550
01:02:09,518 --> 01:02:11,687
Otherwise I wouldn't try...

551
01:02:12,646 --> 01:02:15,816
I left a high power
vacuum cleaner there.

552
01:02:15,816 --> 01:02:18,819
- I see.
- I didn't even look at it.

553
01:02:19,153 --> 01:02:21,655
How do you know
it was a high power vacuum?

554
01:02:22,072 --> 01:02:25,325
- There was a grinder here.
- Where's the wine?

555
01:02:25,617 --> 01:02:28,871
- Did you see the grinder?
- Nope.

556
01:02:30,664 --> 01:02:34,501
It was in a box and there were
some new boots on top of it.

557
01:02:35,836 --> 01:02:37,546
Brand new.

558
01:02:40,007 --> 01:02:43,761
That's how
I knew the vacuum was good.

559
01:02:44,303 --> 01:02:48,015
And I didn't look at it
or the boots.

560
01:02:49,641 --> 01:02:52,978
Because I knew God
was just tempting me.

561
01:02:52,978 --> 01:02:58,317
- Move over.
- Why do you collect this junk?

562
01:02:59,276 --> 01:03:02,029
My son is a disappointment

563
01:03:02,029 --> 01:03:06,033
and I want
to be remembered for something.

564
01:03:06,450 --> 01:03:09,077
You're such a klutz.

565
01:04:23,902 --> 01:04:29,741
Would you go with them?
I'll shoot the breeze with them.

566
01:04:30,534 --> 01:04:34,454
But I'm not going anywhere.
It's awesome here.

567
01:04:34,830 --> 01:04:38,500
- Think so?
- You bet.

568
01:04:38,876 --> 01:04:44,339
There are forty-two
civilizations in the universe,

569
01:04:44,923 --> 01:04:47,426
and we're in last place.

570
01:04:49,011 --> 01:04:51,847
Measured by what?

571
01:04:52,639 --> 01:04:55,559
- Moral maturity...
- Yeah.

572
01:04:56,602 --> 01:04:59,688
We're also the only planet

573
01:04:59,688 --> 01:05:05,485
where procreation
requires only two beings.

574
01:05:05,694 --> 01:05:09,448
So on the other planets
you need three beings?

575
01:05:09,781 --> 01:05:14,286
No, seven. Of various sexes.

576
01:05:15,871 --> 01:05:18,165
There are three of us.

577
01:05:18,165 --> 01:05:23,420
So we'd need four more beings
of totally different sexes.

578
01:05:24,713 --> 01:05:25,589
Right.

579
01:05:27,215 --> 01:05:29,343
Then maybe I will go.

580
01:05:57,204 --> 01:06:00,666
Why are we here, anyway?

581
01:06:06,880 --> 01:06:10,384
- I guess we're waiting for UFOs.
- Right.

582
01:06:11,468 --> 01:06:13,971
I forgot something in the car.

583
01:06:26,483 --> 01:06:30,862
Why are we here, anyway?

584
01:06:34,741 --> 01:06:37,077
You don't really
believe in UFOs.

585
01:06:38,036 --> 01:06:41,081
- Maybe not.
- Then why are you in Prague?

586
01:06:42,165 --> 01:06:46,211
I came here to see Dad.

587
01:06:47,254 --> 01:06:53,218
- Dad? Your Dad?
- Yup. -Is he in this country?

588
01:06:54,678 --> 01:06:55,512
Yup.

589
01:06:56,555 --> 01:06:59,641
- Does he know about you?
- Nope.

590
01:07:02,769 --> 01:07:04,730
Want to tell me about it?

591
01:07:06,773 --> 01:07:07,816
Nope.

592
01:07:11,236 --> 01:07:15,574
And I don't want to start
anything until I see him.

593
01:07:16,700 --> 01:07:20,829
Even though I like you.
Understand?

594
01:07:21,705 --> 01:07:22,706
Of course.

595
01:07:24,166 --> 01:07:28,712
At times it's easier
to see a UFO than your own dad.

596
01:07:53,987 --> 01:07:58,867
So the Macedonian beauty
came here to look for her dad.

597
01:07:58,867 --> 01:08:03,246
He's from the Czech Republic,
and she's never seen him before.

598
01:08:03,538 --> 01:08:07,751
So now I'm going to play
some Macedonian music.

599
01:08:12,839 --> 01:08:15,342
Because at times it's easier
to see a UFO than to live

600
01:08:15,342 --> 01:08:18,804
with the kind of girl
I lived with for three years.

601
01:08:48,834 --> 01:08:52,254
Why did you live with me
if it was that horrible?

602
01:08:53,797 --> 01:08:57,300
- Sorry, we were stoned.
- You can't always make excuses.

603
01:08:57,300 --> 01:09:00,512
- I'm not.
- Know what your problem is?

604
01:09:00,512 --> 01:09:03,098
You've never done
anything for anyone.

605
01:09:03,682 --> 01:09:06,518
You've never given up
anything you like for anyone.

606
01:09:09,521 --> 01:09:11,773
Would you get
a degree for someone?

607
01:09:11,773 --> 01:09:15,068
- For you? -This isn't about me.
- Then who is this about?

608
01:09:15,068 --> 01:09:18,196
- Would you give up
anything at all? -Of course.

609
01:09:18,655 --> 01:09:21,199
Something really important?

610
01:09:21,491 --> 01:09:25,954
Do you want me
to jump off a bridge for you?

611
01:09:26,621 --> 01:09:31,126
No, I just wanted you
to be brave about our break-up.

612
01:09:32,002 --> 01:09:35,255
So I'd have a reason to respect
you so I could come back to you.

613
01:09:35,255 --> 01:09:39,968
So you wanted to come back to me
because I broke up with you?

614
01:09:40,594 --> 01:09:42,470
- Yeah.
- That's great.

615
01:09:43,972 --> 01:09:46,808
You're just like your mother.

616
01:10:04,034 --> 01:10:04,784
What?

617
01:10:25,931 --> 01:10:30,894
As Station Manager I am
responsible for what you play.

618
01:10:32,646 --> 01:10:35,857
I don't care about your break-up
or your contest. No one does.

619
01:10:36,733 --> 01:10:39,444
Tell me why you play this stuff.

620
01:10:43,615 --> 01:10:47,452
My mother is ten times worse
than what you've been playing.

621
01:10:48,620 --> 01:10:51,039
Radio is no private matter.

622
01:10:52,707 --> 01:10:56,586
If I hear this stuff again,
you can pack it in. Get it?

623
01:10:57,337 --> 01:10:57,879
Yes.

624
01:11:05,470 --> 01:11:08,306
I was afraid
we'd never meet again.

625
01:11:11,226 --> 01:11:14,145
Nah, I knew we would.

626
01:11:15,397 --> 01:11:17,691
How did you know that?

627
01:11:18,275 --> 01:11:22,529
Because the guy
pinned in the car was a sign.

628
01:11:24,155 --> 01:11:25,532
A sign?

629
01:11:27,158 --> 01:11:32,455
We find a guy pinned in his car
the first time we meet.

630
01:11:33,373 --> 01:11:37,335
He was pinned
in a car he'd rolled.

631
01:11:38,503 --> 01:11:40,839
Didn't that seem
like a sign to you?

632
01:11:42,048 --> 01:11:44,718
Yeah, I guess so.

633
01:11:47,804 --> 01:11:52,809
It's a clear sign that
something's going on between us.

634
01:11:55,770 --> 01:12:02,986
The fact that you're high is
a sign you shouldn't be driving.

635
01:12:05,947 --> 01:12:09,784
Get a load of these buildings.

636
01:12:10,410 --> 01:12:12,912
Aren't they awesome?

637
01:12:15,915 --> 01:12:18,418
What city is this? Dubrovnik?

638
01:12:20,754 --> 01:12:26,259
- This is Prague, you moron.
- I know. I was just testing you.

639
01:12:27,677 --> 01:12:30,847
This is where I was born.
This is where I live.

640
01:12:32,891 --> 01:12:37,812
But today it seems new.
It's really nice.

641
01:12:45,612 --> 01:12:49,574
Tourists flip out
over these buildings.

642
01:12:54,704 --> 01:12:58,208
You can rip me off
just like you do to tourists.

643
01:12:58,625 --> 01:13:01,002
It sounds like
you're saying he steals.

644
01:13:02,420 --> 01:13:05,840
- So you really steal, huh?
- Knock it off.

645
01:13:07,550 --> 01:13:10,720
Why? Let him steal.
It's awesome.

646
01:13:15,725 --> 01:13:19,938
Where's he going? How can
he drive from out there?

647
01:13:29,781 --> 01:13:30,824
Ouch!

648
01:14:15,660 --> 01:14:18,371
The Golden Age of Moving
is coming.

649
01:14:18,705 --> 01:14:22,876
More and more people are moving
to more and more new places.

650
01:14:23,710 --> 01:14:26,754
I'm afraid of how it'll turn out.

651
01:14:27,964 --> 01:14:32,844
But I'm not getting in the way.
I want to move with the times!

652
01:14:34,471 --> 01:14:37,474
- What do you want to be?
- A mover.

653
01:14:39,309 --> 01:14:44,898
- You already are one.
- Awesome. Then I'll keep my job!

654
01:15:21,100 --> 01:15:22,894
My sincere condolences...

655
01:15:47,085 --> 01:15:49,671
Wow! Awesome hose.

656
01:16:00,390 --> 01:16:03,184
- My condolences.
- Do I know you?

657
01:16:05,353 --> 01:16:07,021
I'm Ondrej.

658
01:16:12,735 --> 01:16:19,450
Of course, Lenka's husband.
She's looking for you.

659
01:16:19,951 --> 01:16:24,038
Come in.
Look at all the junk Mom had.

660
01:16:24,289 --> 01:16:26,791
It's that psychopath again.

661
01:16:30,795 --> 01:16:33,506
