Holy shit!

714
01:24:26,479 --> 01:24:28,439
This is unreal!

715
01:24:35,154 --> 01:24:38,407
That was warped. Wasn't it?

716
01:27:05,763 --> 01:27:07,056
Please...

717
01:27:08,641 --> 01:27:10,434
I love you.

718
01:27:11,143 --> 01:27:14,063
I think of you in so many places

719
01:27:14,063 --> 01:27:17,608
that I can't even name them all.

720
01:27:21,445 --> 01:27:23,739
I love you more than anything.

721
01:27:26,992 --> 01:27:29,245
Why did you film this?

722
01:27:31,247 --> 01:27:34,208
I don't know.
I found it interesting.

723
01:27:35,501 --> 01:27:37,086
Interesting?

724
01:27:38,045 --> 01:27:39,129
Yup.

725
01:27:43,592 --> 01:27:48,555
- It seems sad to me.
- It is sad.

726
01:27:51,850 --> 01:27:56,689
Maybe that's my problem.
I find sad things fascinating.

727
01:27:58,315 --> 01:28:02,361
Without sadness I feel nothing,
and I can't change.

728
01:28:03,737 --> 01:28:07,950
- That's quite sad, isn't it?
- Yes, but it's also fascinating.

729
01:28:13,205 --> 01:28:15,249
You are a real idiot.

730
01:28:21,505 --> 01:28:24,049
"I'm sorry, Hanka"

731
01:29:01,045 --> 01:29:02,379
Scram!

732
01:29:04,298 --> 01:29:08,385
We all need relationships.
Someone who loves you.

733
01:29:08,761 --> 01:29:11,764
Someone who'll
caress you when you're down.

734
01:29:13,432 --> 01:29:17,978
The world might be awesome,
but sometimes it stinks.

735
01:29:18,812 --> 01:29:24,777
And Hanka's sensitive.
She's totally awesome.

736
01:29:25,402 --> 01:29:29,573
I told her I love her
and I want to live with her.

737
01:29:30,449 --> 01:29:33,243
Live with her?
You already have a girlfriend.

738
01:29:36,205 --> 01:29:39,458
- Say what?
- C'mon, Alice.

739
01:29:39,708 --> 01:29:42,836
- Alice who?
- You tell me.

740
01:29:43,796 --> 01:29:49,426
I wouldn't...
Oh yeah, Alice. But we broke up.

741
01:29:50,344 --> 01:29:52,096
No, you didn't.

742
01:29:53,597 --> 01:29:56,809
But we saw her off
at the train station.

743
01:29:58,227 --> 01:30:01,397
She just went
to Germany to see her aunt.

744
01:30:02,272 --> 01:30:04,942
You're a total waste case.

745
01:30:04,942 --> 01:30:07,820
You can't even remember
who you're going out with.

746
01:30:07,820 --> 01:30:12,199
Do you even know your own name?
Listen, quit smoking pot.

747
01:30:15,661 --> 01:30:18,455
Do you want me to go schizo?

748
01:30:37,933 --> 01:30:40,644
"I'll wait for you"

749
01:30:54,992 --> 01:30:57,494
I have to tell you something.

750
01:30:58,620 --> 01:31:01,415
I thought we'd start going out,

751
01:31:01,415 --> 01:31:06,503
but the guys said
I already had a girlfriend.

752
01:31:07,838 --> 01:31:09,798
- Which guys?
- From the band.

753
01:31:10,799 --> 01:31:13,844
Then it all came back to me.

754
01:31:15,095 --> 01:31:17,931
I'd totally forgotten about her.

755
01:31:21,393 --> 01:31:28,066
- You're joking, right?
- No, I'm not. I know it's awful.

756
01:31:29,860 --> 01:31:33,572
I'm sorry,
but put yourself in my place.

757
01:31:33,572 --> 01:31:38,118
Life's a bitch. Everything
has turned against us.

758
01:31:39,495 --> 01:31:45,959
I want to cry. I love you,
but I promised to stay with her.

759
01:31:48,003 --> 01:31:50,547
I remember making that decision.

760
01:31:53,592 --> 01:31:58,514
- I don't want to hurt anyone.
- You don't want to hurt anyone?

761
01:31:59,389 --> 01:32:03,519
- I'm sorry.
- It's all that pot you smoke!

762
01:32:03,936 --> 01:32:06,021
It's that lifestyle of yours!

763
01:32:14,530 --> 01:32:17,324
This is the last thing
I'm gonna play for you.

764
01:32:17,324 --> 01:32:20,911
This is also the last tape
I have of my girlfriend.

765
01:32:21,245 --> 01:32:25,290
This is her cough
from March 3, 1997.

766
01:32:25,582 --> 01:32:29,002
You can see how long
we were together.

767
01:32:30,963 --> 01:32:34,841
I guess we hurt each other.
But in any event...

768
01:32:38,011 --> 01:32:42,224
Here's a beautiful cough.

769
01:33:48,790 --> 01:33:52,169
Where have you been?
We started without you.

770
01:33:52,377 --> 01:33:53,795
Where have you been?

771
01:33:56,214 --> 01:33:57,924
We started without you.

772
01:34:02,346 --> 01:34:03,138
Come on.

773
01:34:06,224 --> 01:34:06,892
Sit down.

774
01:34:11,188 --> 01:34:14,441
- What is this?
- Beef. -With cranberries.

775
01:34:16,109 --> 01:34:17,903
No, thanks. I'm not hungry.

776
01:34:18,445 --> 01:34:22,324
This is beef.
Have some more dumplings.

777
01:34:23,825 --> 01:34:28,080
They want to see how we eat.
Isn't this in the contract?

778
01:34:30,957 --> 01:34:35,379
- Can I talk to you in private?
- Later, okay?

779
01:34:35,504 --> 01:34:38,882
The father is indicating
that they can talk later.

780
01:34:39,174 --> 01:34:42,886
What the hell is this?
What's she saying?

781
01:34:43,178 --> 01:34:45,722
- Watch your language!
- Stop snapping at me!

782
01:34:46,139 --> 01:34:49,768
The daughter is surprised
by the unusual situation.

783
01:34:51,520 --> 01:34:53,980
I'm not afraid to slap you!

784
01:34:54,815 --> 01:34:59,236
I came to see you because I feel
awful and I need to talk to you.

785
01:35:02,614 --> 01:35:05,200
Yet what do I find here?

786
01:35:07,661 --> 01:35:11,790
Do you know why you feel awful?
It's that lifestyle of yours.

787
01:35:12,290 --> 01:35:14,418
The daughter wants advice on how

788
01:35:18,672 --> 01:35:21,425
to deal with the fact that

789
01:35:23,009 --> 01:35:25,846
a married man is stalking her.

790
01:35:26,012 --> 01:35:29,558
- It those friends of yours.
- You don't even know them.

791
01:35:29,558 --> 01:35:31,518
Seeing them is enough.

792
01:35:31,852 --> 01:35:36,356
Isn't it odd for a girl
your age to move all the time?

793
01:35:37,190 --> 01:35:38,233
Quiet!

794
01:35:38,859 --> 01:35:43,822
- Seeing you breaks my heart.
- You break my heart too, Mom.

795
01:35:43,822 --> 01:35:45,198
Stop it!

796
01:35:51,705 --> 01:35:53,790
This is unbearable.

797
01:35:54,499 --> 01:35:58,336
The parents object to having
this kind of discussion today.

798
01:35:58,587 --> 01:36:02,632
Kindly realize that
life isn't that easy.

799
01:36:03,175 --> 01:36:04,551
- I see.
- What?

800
01:36:05,761 --> 01:36:10,056
You have an obligation.
We've had to make sacrifices.

801
01:36:10,849 --> 01:36:13,560
Well I have, out of love!

802
01:36:15,228 --> 01:36:19,733
You don't even know what that
means because your friends...

803
01:36:19,733 --> 01:36:24,321
- ... never make sacrifices for you.
- I don't want them to!

804
01:36:24,988 --> 01:36:28,992
And they don't!
You people don't live life.

805
01:36:28,992 --> 01:36:30,577
You just slice it!

806
01:36:32,496 --> 01:36:38,251
The mother thinks the daughter
is to blame for her own problems.

807
01:38:56,765 --> 01:38:59,351
I like women as people.

808
01:39:00,060 --> 01:39:03,021
I'm just not going
to sleep with them anymore.

809
01:39:03,021 --> 01:39:07,692
If I ever do meet a girl,
for the first 146 days

810
01:39:08,151 --> 01:39:10,445
we're just going to talk.

811
01:39:10,445 --> 01:39:13,615
146 days. That's important.
It can't be less than that.

812
01:39:15,617 --> 01:39:19,829
Then maybe I'll give her a kiss.

813
01:39:22,374 --> 01:39:26,169
But until I find that kind
of girl I'm going to be alone.

814
01:39:27,671 --> 01:39:32,175
Not everyone has the chance
to be alone like I have.

815
01:39:39,641 --> 01:39:42,227
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

816
01:39:43,645 --> 01:39:45,939
Have you already started?

817
01:39:46,481 --> 01:39:48,483
- Did you wash your hands?
- Yes.

818
01:39:56,157 --> 01:39:59,327
- I saw the video.
- Which video?

819
01:39:59,661 --> 01:40:04,499
From Robert's party.
I was quite shocked.

820
01:40:04,833 --> 01:40:08,336
It was just an ordinary party.

821
01:40:09,379 --> 01:40:12,841
You have a few drinks,
and then act crazy.

822
01:40:12,841 --> 01:40:18,221
You dance and laugh.
Should I pack my things?

823
01:40:19,180 --> 01:40:22,684
Of course not.
Have a seat.

824
01:40:25,895 --> 01:40:28,273
I think we have
a good relationship.

825
01:40:29,566 --> 01:40:31,818
- Do you?
- Of course.

826
01:40:33,611 --> 01:40:38,324
You buy us nice Christmas gifts.
You don't smoke or drink.

827
01:40:39,034 --> 01:40:41,953
You're faithful to me, reliable.

828
01:40:43,413 --> 01:40:45,081
And you love us.

829
01:40:46,750 --> 01:40:50,462
- Do you think so?
- Of course you love us.

830
01:40:55,050 --> 01:40:58,803
- Did you think you loved her?
- Yes, I did.

831
01:41:01,056 --> 01:41:04,893
Sometimes it's hard to figure
out what you want on your own.

832
01:41:04,893 --> 01:41:08,563
You think you want
to live with someone else.

833
01:41:08,855 --> 01:41:14,903
Yet what you really want
is to dress up as a plumber.

834
01:41:16,738 --> 01:41:18,740
Why, that's me.

835
01:41:19,240 --> 01:41:25,997
I didn't know the problem was
your attraction to overalls.

836
01:41:29,167 --> 01:41:31,628
You can wear them at home.

837
01:41:37,884 --> 01:41:43,515
Thanks, but I don't think
that's the main problem.

838
01:41:43,973 --> 01:41:47,560
Perhaps the hospital would
even let you wear them to work.

839
01:41:51,606 --> 01:41:57,237
- No. Well, maybe.
- But promise you'll think about it.

840
01:42:00,782 --> 01:42:03,451
Fine, I'll think about it.

841
01:42:05,286 --> 01:42:07,163
- Bon appetit.
- Bon appetit.

842
01:42:09,290 --> 01:42:10,625
Bon appetit!

843
01:42:12,377 --> 01:42:17,298
I get high because the world
is cruel and people are lonely.

844
01:42:18,174 --> 01:42:23,596
I work so I can buy drugs
that make people seem kind,

845
01:42:24,097 --> 01:42:28,059
friendly, free, and beautiful.

846
01:42:30,728 --> 01:42:36,276
Trouble is these drugs probably
caused me to hurt someone.

847
01:42:37,694 --> 01:42:41,823
So it doesn't make sense
for me to do them anymore.

848
01:42:43,283 --> 01:42:47,620
I've had it with drugs.
I'm giving up weed.

849
01:42:50,874 --> 01:42:52,792
This is my last joint.

850
01:42:54,961 --> 01:42:56,963
I'm not even going to finish it.

851
01:43:37,378 --> 01:43:43,635
- What's she like?
- She's a bit selfish and tough,

852
01:43:43,968 --> 01:43:47,222
and she never gives up
without a fight.

853
01:43:47,555 --> 01:43:52,018
- Is it even worth the effort?
- Yeah. Give it a try.

854
01:44:13,206 --> 01:44:14,415
- Hi!
- Hi!

855
01:44:15,708 --> 01:44:17,710
Pretty good, huh?

856
01:44:19,879 --> 01:44:25,510
It occurred to me that the guy
I took to the hospital...

857
01:44:25,969 --> 01:44:29,639
- ...really could've been a sign.
- What kind of sign?

858
01:45:11,681 --> 01:45:14,684
English subtitles
by Lisette Saint Germain

859
